{"parse":{"title":"Dedication (publishing)","pageid":25590689,"revid":848293909,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Dedication_CAGSTAU_book.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/Dedication_CAGSTAU_book.png/350px-Dedication_CAGSTAU_book.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"59\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/06/Dedication_CAGSTAU_book.png 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"474\" data-file-height=\"80\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Dedication_CAGSTAU_book.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Book dedication to a group of people.</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>dedication</b> is the expression of friendly connection or thanks by the author towards another person. The dedication has its own place on the <i>dedication page</i> and is part of the <a href=\"/wiki/Book_design#Front_matter\" title=\"Book design\">front matter</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Position_and_function_of_the_dedication\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Position and function  of the dedication</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Themes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Themes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Handwritten_dedication\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Handwritten dedication</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Position_and_function_of_the_dedication\">Position and function  of the dedication</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dedication_(publishing)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Position and function of the dedication\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In newer books, the dedication is located on a <i>dedication page</i> on its own, usually on the <a href=\"/wiki/Recto_and_verso\" title=\"Recto and verso\">recto page</a> after the <a href=\"/wiki/Title_page\" title=\"Title page\">main title page</a> inside the <a href=\"/wiki/Front_matter\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Front matter\">front matter</a>. It can occupy one or multiple lines depending on its importance. It can also be \"in a longer version as a dedication letter or dedication preface at the book's beginning\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Nowadays, the dedication's function is mainly part of the self-portrayal of the author in front of his or her readers.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dedication_(publishing)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg/220px-Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"295\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg/330px-Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg/440px-Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"448\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Orfeo_libretto_d%C3%A9dicace.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The dedication of <i>Orfeo</i> by <a href=\"/wiki/Claudio_Monteverdi\" title=\"Claudio Monteverdi\">Monteverdi</a>, 1609</div></div></div>\n<p>Evidence of dedications is provided back into the <a href=\"/wiki/Classical_antiquity\" title=\"Classical antiquity\">Classical antiquity</a>. Besides the wish to express their gratitude towards a certain person, the authors often had also other reasons to dedicate their work to a particular person. Well into the 18th century, it was not usual for <a href=\"/wiki/Publisher\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Publisher\">publishers</a> to remunerate the authors; authors tended to be paid or remunerated as one element of a <a href=\"/wiki/Patron-client_relationship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Patron-client relationship\">patron-client relationship</a>, in which the author-client paid tribute, in the dedication, to his or her patron.  A typical writer dedicated \"their book to a high standing personality -- to <a href=\"/wiki/F%C3%BCrst\" title=\"F\u00fcrst\">F\u00fcrsts</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Bishop\" title=\"Bishop\">bishops</a> -- or to a city and tried to gain some money through this practice\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Hiller2002_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hiller2002-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In many cases the petitioner was lucky and received a gift from the patron. In some cases, the writer groveled before the patron and a formal dedication \"contained often a very elaborate and submissive affection\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Hiller2002_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Hiller2002-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In some cases not only the authors tried to get some money, but also the printers tried through dedications to cover a part of their costs.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Themes\">Themes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dedication_(publishing)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Themes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A book dedication can provide a fascinating glimpse into the life and times of the author.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> For example, <a href=\"/wiki/Lord_Byron\" title=\"Lord Byron\">Lord Byron</a> (1788\u20131824) engaged in a famous feud with <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Southey\" title=\"Robert Southey\">Robert Southey</a>, who was then England's <a href=\"/wiki/Poet_Laureate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Poet Laureate\">Poet Laureate</a>. Byron wrote a mocking 17-verse dedication to his epic poem <i><a href=\"/wiki/Don_Juan_(Byron)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Don Juan (Byron)\">Don Juan</a></i> in which he savagely pilloried Southey as a dull, reactionary \"warbler\" who had abandoned his political principles for favor and financial reward.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Throughout time, book dedications were used to make political statements or to condemn war and inequality. Author <a href=\"/wiki/Toni_Morrison\" title=\"Toni Morrison\">Toni Morrison</a> dedicated <i><a href=\"/wiki/Beloved_(novel)\" title=\"Beloved (novel)\">Beloved</a></i>, her 1987 <a href=\"/wiki/Pulitzer_Prize\" title=\"Pulitzer Prize\">Pulitzer Prize</a>-winning novel about a fugitive slave who killed her daughter, to \"Sixty Million and more.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Furthermore, book dedications reflect the tastes and mores of society. Whereas many Elizabethan dedications were erudite and witty, some modern authors have abandoned literary pretense, sometimes using profanity to shock or amuse their audiences.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Handwritten_dedication\">Handwritten dedication</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dedication_(publishing)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Handwritten dedication\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The dedication is not to be confounded with the handwritten dedication of a single copy: the <a href=\"/wiki/Presentation_copy\" title=\"Presentation copy\">presentation copy</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dedication_(publishing)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Homage_(arts)\" title=\"Homage (arts)\">Homage</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Book_design#Front_matter\" title=\"Book design\">Front matter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Prologue\" title=\"Prologue\">Prologue</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Paratext\" title=\"Paratext\">Paratext</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Dedication_(publishing)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Ursula Rautenberger (ed.): <i>Reclams Sachlexikon des Buches</i>, p. 148.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Hiller2002-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Hiller2002_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Hiller2002_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Citation after Helmut Hiller, Stephan F\u00fcssel: <i>W\u00f6rterbuch des Buches</i>. 6. Auflage. Vittorio Klostermann, Frankfurt am Main, 2002. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/3-465-032209\" title=\"Special:BookSources/3-465-032209\">3-465-032209</a>, p. 82.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Barnes, Patricia (2015). <i>Tender, Tawdry &amp; Timeless Book Dedications</i>. <a href=\"/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number\" title=\"Amazon Standard Identification Number\">ASIN</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.amazon.com/dp/B00VZ2YRM4\">B00VZ2YRM4</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0989870839\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0989870839\">0989870839</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tender%2C+Tawdry+%26+Timeless+Book+Dedications&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.isbn=0989870839&amp;rft.aulast=Barnes&amp;rft.aufirst=Patricia&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADedication+%28publishing%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Barnes (2015). <i>Tender, Tawdry &amp; Timeless Book Dedications</i>. pp.&#160;281\u2013288.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tender%2C+Tawdry+%26+Timeless+Book+Dedications&amp;rft.pages=281-288&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.au=Barnes&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADedication+%28publishing%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Barnes (2015). <i>Tender, Tawdry &amp; Timeless Book Dedications</i>. p.&#160;173.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tender%2C+Tawdry+%26+Timeless+Book+Dedications&amp;rft.pages=173&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.au=Barnes&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADedication+%28publishing%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Barnes (2015). <i>Tender, Tawdry &amp; Timeless Book Dedications</i>. p.&#160;13.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tender%2C+Tawdry+%26+Timeless+Book+Dedications&amp;rft.pages=13&amp;rft.date=2015&am